{
  "text": "Our previous studies used ultrasonography to assess whole arterial BF Ab hemodynamics: BF Ab was obtained by subtracting blood flow in the bilateral proximal femoral arteries [left femoral artery (LFA) and right femoral artery (RFA)] from blood flow in the upper abdominal aorta (Ao) above the coeliac artery bifurcation [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
